snippet: No charges will be brought against Archbishop John Nienstedt of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of St. Paul and Minneapolis, who was accused by a boy of inappropriately touching him.
abstract: Prosecutors say there is insufficient evidence to charge Archbishop John Nienstedt of Roman Catholic Archdiocese of St Paul and Minneapolis, who was accused by a boy of inappropriately touching his buttocks during a group photo session.
lead_paragraph: No charges will be brought against Archbishop John Nienstedt of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of St. Paul and Minneapolis, who was accused by a boy of inappropriately touching him.

headline.main: Minnesota: Archbishop Will Not Face Charges
headline.print_headline: Minnesota: Archbishop Will Not Face Charges
